  "doc_id": "34858",
  "text": "From these experiments, we conclude that overlapping rectangles are the primary source of difficulty for NGE and that BNGE was the best variant of NGE that we studied. Further experiments reported in [CITATION_1] show that BNGE commits most of its errors outside of all hyperrectangles. By using kNN to classify all test examples that fall outside any hyperrectangle, a hybrid method of BNGE and kNN attains classification accuracy comparable to kNN alone--but with a large improvement in classification speed.",
